## Architecture

### Page-views pattern (mandatory)

Three layers — never collapse them:

1. **Pages** (`src/pages/{{DEFAULT_LOCALE}}/`) — Thin wrappers (≤5 lines). Import a PageView, nothing else.
2. **Page-Views** (`src/page-views/`) — All markup, data fetching, and translations.
3. **Layouts** (`src/layouts/`) — Page shell (html, head, body, header, footer).

### i18n

- All UI strings in `src/i18n/{{DEFAULT_LOCALE}}.json` + `src/i18n/{{SECONDARY_LOCALE}}.json`
- Locale JSONs use flat dotted keys (`"notFound.title"`) — the default locale file defines the `MessageKey` type in `src/lib/i18n.ts`, so a typo in a `tl()` call is a compile error
- Use `createTranslator(Astro.currentLocale)` in every component — never pass `lang` or `tl` as props
- Detect locale via `Astro.currentLocale` — never parse URLs
- `prefixDefaultLocale: true` — all routes prefixed
- `redirectToDefaultLocale: false` + explicit `redirects: { '/': '/{{DEFAULT_LOCALE}}' }`

### Content collections

- Config at `src/content.config.ts` (NOT `src/content/config.ts`)
- `glob()` loaders, Zod schemas
- Single collection per type with locale subfolders: `articles/{{DEFAULT_LOCALE}}/`, `articles/{{SECONDARY_LOCALE}}/`
- `translationKey` links content across locales
- Flexible `tags: string[]` — no fixed category enums
- `draft: true` keeps an entry out of listings, feeds, and sitemaps

### Utility layer (`src/lib/`)

- `content.ts` — all content collection queries (page-views never call `getCollection()` directly)
- `urls.ts` — all URL builders (components never concatenate locale prefixes by hand)
- `format.ts` — locale-aware date/number formatting via `Intl` (never a date library)
- `i18n.ts` — `createTranslator()` factory + the `MessageKey` type

